SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 37
BY SENATOR FESI
HEALTH CARE. Requests the surgeon general to develop a plan relative to informed
consent.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To request the surgeon general to review Louisiana's informed consent laws and submit a
3 report to the legislature on whether any gaps exist in current laws.
4 WHEREAS, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, while
5 there is a requirement for certain vaccine information to be given to a patient prior to an
6 immunization, there is no federal requirement for informed consent relating to
7 immunizations; and
8 WHEREAS, the National Childhood Vaccine Injury Act of 1986, as amended,
9 created the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program, in response to lawsuits against
10 vaccine manufacturers and healthcare providers that threatened to cause vaccine shortages
11 and reduce vaccination rates; and
12 WHEREAS, one component of the program is a requirement for a healthcare
13 provider to provide a copy of the current Vaccine Information Statement (VIS) to the legal
14 representative of any child or to any other individual receiving certain vaccines; and
15 WHEREAS, while a VIS provides information, informed consent is an ethical and
16 legal process involving a discussion and explicit, voluntary patient permission to proceed
17 with any medical or surgical procedure, which may be required by state law; and
18 WHEREAS, Louisiana has uniform consent laws and medical consent laws as
